*I WILL SHIP to FFL*

Less than 500 rounds shot through it, It still looks damn near new. Before I even shot it, I purchased new old stock FEG standard wood grip for the front and new old stock FEG "fat" pistol grip for the rear. I acquired a generic eastern europe beech wood stock and refinished in a light poly coat stain because FEG hungarian stocks are $150-200. It doesn't perfectly match but looks and feels a hell of a lot better than the garbage black plastic stock that came on it. 
The receiver is hungarian FEG as is the bolt and carrier, trunnions, gas system, etc. The barrel and FCG are US as well as the muzzle break. This will still meet 922r compliance with american magazines.Shoots very accurately. great trigger. Over all I love it and is probably the most affordable way to get a military grade fighting rifle, by far. I would consider keeping it if it had the proper AMD63 long gas system but I'm too much of a perfectionist. I didn't mind it having the AMD65 short gas system, obviously, since it was such a great price.
 
Classic is now selling these on sale for $450. Shipping is roughly $20 for the rifle. I have roughly $100 into the wood furniture. Thus, total this rifle would currently cost 570 new in it's form. Asking $500. Obviously for trades, gun values will be equalized by cash on which ever side needs to add cash. More than welcome to test shoot in person. Must have Valid AZ DL, preferably CCW licence.
